HARARE - Renowned Zimbabwean academic George Kahari has been nominated as International Educator of the Year 2017 by the England-based International Biographical Centre of Cambridge (IBC). &ldquo;This prestigious award will be made available only to a few illustrious individuals whose achievements and leadership stand out in the international community,&rdquo; IBC director-general Nicholas Law said in a letter to Kahari. Kahari, who has previously served as Zimbabwe&rsquo;s Ambassador to Germany, Italy and Czechoslovakia, was in 2012 nominated into the list of top 100 educators by the IBC in recognition of his &ldquo;contribution in their field to engender influence on a local, national or international basis&rdquo;.&nbsp;